{
  "texts": [
    "However, during the last two years, the implementation of Artificial intelligence and support of vector machines in the diagnosis and prognosis of breast cancer have paved the way for earlier detection of breast cancer.",
    "Our observations indicate that institutions in developed nations rarely take the lead in partnering with counterparts in developing and underdeveloped regions.",
    "Collaborations with lower-income countries or institutions with less research funding reveal gaps in the availability and accessibility of AI-based diagnostic tools, shedding light on the disparities within this global research agenda.",
    "[38, 39] Developed nations prefer to collaborate with institutions that match or surpass their own in terms of infrastructure and intellectual capability.",
    "Therefore, countries with superior infrastructure and economies must engage in collaborative projects with skilled intellectuals and their institutions from developing and underdeveloped nations, leveraging current technologies to create a global AI-driven breast cancer healthcare network."
  ]
}